  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fresh Water Wells &amp; Hygiene Education in Aweil, South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Water for South Sudan (WFSS) drilling team will work with county officials and local villages and chiefs to determine the best placement of water wells. Villagers will be responsible for wells upon completion, and must provide villagers willing to be trained in maintenance and upkeep of the well.

WFSS Hygiene Team will travel with the drilling team and train eight people in each village (four men and four women) to improve hygiene practices. Activities include education in how germs spread, keeping cooking areas and utensils clean, and will also focus on personal hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for South Sudan will drill up to 40 new water wells and provide hygiene education in Aweil State and Aweil East.</narrative>
  </description>
